The Tendencia winds down through the autumn with the discipline it showed all along: files buried, purged men placed two hundred at a time in workshops and cooperatives, the young cadre steered into the teachers' and university unions where the next round will be fought. Galván — sixty-one, expelled, blacklisted — keeps writing until his heart quits in 1980, and his wake will fill a street. The defeat is total and unusually fertile: for the next decade, every independent union current in Mexico is run by somebody who learned the trade in the TD.
